# PROMPT – Rules to build screen

You are a **Builder**.  
**Inputs**: `design.json`, `spec.md`, `plan.md`, `guides/UI_MAPPING_GUIDE.md`.  
**Output**: a set of Flutter files according to `plan.md`.

---

## Hard requirements

- **No guessing**: any color or style used must come from `tokens.colors` or explicit `component.style`. Never invent hex values.
- **Respect semantics** found in `design.json`: `variant`, `placement`, `widthMode`, `group.{alignment,distribution,maxWidth}`, `typographyRef`, `style.transform`, `leadingIcon`, slider visual properties.
- **Deterministic keys**: every rendered widget must have `Key('<screenName>__<component-id>')`.
- **Guardrail**: if `qa.confidenceGlobal` exists and is below the configured threshold, emit a build warning (or stop if required by contracts).

---

## Theme bootstrap (from tokens)

Build `ThemeData` and `ColorScheme` directly from `tokens.colors` and `tokens.typography`.
- `AppBar.backgroundColor` = `tokens.colors.headerBackgroundDark` if present, else `colorScheme.primary`.
- `SliderTheme` uses `activeTrack`, `inactiveTrack`, `thumbColor`, `trackHeight` when provided.

> Refer to `guides/UI_MAPPING_GUIDE.md` for helper mappers (color lookup, radius, text styles).

```dart
ThemeData buildTheme(Tokens t) { /* see guide: color scheme + slider theme */ }
TextTheme buildTextTheme(Tokens t) { /* map typographyRef to TextTheme */ }
```

---

## Mapping rules (generic)

### Text
- Compute `final copy = applyTransform(node.text, node.style?.transform)` then render `Text(copy, style: resolveTextStyle(node, tokens))`.

### Buttons by `variant`
- `cta` → `ElevatedButton(.icon)` with background = `tokens.colors.cta` (fallback: `tokens.colors.primary`), foreground = `tokens.colors.onPrimary`.
- `primary` → `ElevatedButton` bg = `tokens.colors.primary`, fg = `tokens.colors.onPrimary`.
- `secondary` → `OutlinedButton` with `BorderSide(color = style.borderColor or tokens.colors.border, width = style.borderWidth or 1)`.
- `ghost` → `TextButton` with foreground = `style.color` or `colorScheme.primary`.
- If `leadingIcon` is present, use the `.icon` constructor and resolve the icon from `iconName`.

### IconButton with shape
- If `style.radius` and/or `style.borderWidth`/`borderColor` exist, wrap `IconButton` in a decorated `Container` enforcing size, border and radius.

### Placement & width
- `widthMode:"fill"` ⇒ wrap with `Expanded`.  
- `widthMode:"intrinsic"` ⇒ size to content.  
- `placement:"start|center|end"` ⇒ use `Align` inside the parent axis to position accordingly.

### Group alignment & maxWidth
- For containers/cards with a `group` block:
  - If `alignment:"center"` ⇒ wrap child with `Center`.
  - If `alignment:"end"` ⇒ wrap child with `Align(alignment: Alignment.centerRight)`.
  - If `maxWidth > 0` ⇒ `ConstrainedBox(BoxConstraints(maxWidth: ...))` around the group.
  - Map `distribution` to `MainAxisAlignment.start|spaceBetween|spaceAround|end`.

### Slider
- Render with a `SliderTheme` reflecting `activeTrack`, `inactiveTrack`, `thumbColor`, `trackHeight` from `node.style` when provided.
- Set initial `value` from `valueNormalized` if present (range [0,1]).

### Icons
- When `iconName` starts with `material.`, map to `Icons.*`. Otherwise use a registry/provider function.

### Keys
- Every widget uses `key: Key('\${screenName}__\${node.id}')` for stability and testing.

---

## Renderer skeleton (pseudocode)

```dart
Widget buildNode(Node n, Tokens t, String screen) {
  switch (n.type) {
    case "Container":
    case "Card":
      final child = buildFlex(n, t, screen);
      return groupWrap(child, n.group);
    case "Text":
      return Text(applyTransform(n.text, n.style?.transform ?? "none"),
        key: compKey(screen, n),
        style: resolveTextStyle(n, t));
    case "Button":
      return place(buildButton(n, t), n);
    case "IconButton":
      final raw = needsShape(n) ? shapedIconButton(n, t) : IconButton(
        key: compKey(screen, n), onPressed: (){}, icon: buildIcon(n, t));
      return place(raw, n);
    case "Slider":
      return place(buildSlider(n, t), n);
    case "Icon":
      return Icon(resolveIconData(n.iconName), key: compKey(screen, n));
    default:
      return const SizedBox.shrink();
  }
}
```

---

## Acceptance checklist (auto-verify)

- [ ] Every widget has a deterministic `Key`.
- [ ] No color outside `tokens.colors` or explicit `style` on the component.
- [ ] Button `variant` applied (`cta/primary/secondary/ghost`) and visible in code.
- [ ] `placement` & `widthMode` respected (Expanded vs intrinsic + Align).
- [ ] Groups with `alignment:center` are centered and constrained by `maxWidth` when provided.
- [ ] `leadingIcon` rendered where present; label `transform` respected.
- [ ] Sliders reflect `activeTrack/inactiveTrack/thumbColor/trackHeight`.
- [ ] Build warns if `qa.confidenceGlobal` (when present) is below threshold.
